Job Title: API Integration Support Specialist - Mulesoft, IBM, Federal Govt
Ad Text:
5-month initial contract + 12-month extension option

High-impact API integration role with a Federal Government agency

Rewarding hourly rates $

A prominent Federal Government agency is seeking an experienced API Integration Support Specialist (Integration Analyst) to join their dynamic Digital Services team. This is a fantastic opportunity to work on innovative ICT solutions and contribute to the delivery of streamlined digital services for millions of Australians. The API Integration Support Specialist (Integration Analyst) will be offered an initial 5-month contract with a 12-month extension, open to candidates in NSW, with flexible hybrid work arrangements available.

The successful API Integration Support Specialist will be responsible for, but not limited to:

Manage API lifecycle: register, configure, and maintain APIs using MuleSoft and IBM API Connect.

Monitor and troubleshoot: conduct API testing, monitor performance, and resolve issues with technical teams and vendors.

Provide technical support: assist with authentication problems, prepare reports/dashboards, and maintain documentation.

Apply best practices: follow ITIL methodology for incident management and service requests.

Collaborate in Agile delivery: participate in daily stand-ups, sprints, and contribute to system improvements.

To be successful, the API Integration Support Specialist will demonstrate:

2–3 years’ experience in API integration and related technologies.

Strong understanding of API concepts with adaptability to complex environments.

Proven experience in Agile/Scrum and DevOps, including CI/CD support.

Excellent communication and collaboration skills; MuleSoft or IBM API Connect experience desirable.

This is a great opportunity with a Federal Government Department and to join a supportive team! The successful API Integration Support Specialist will be offered a 5-month contract + 12-month extension option! If you have the required skills and experience, APPLY NOW. Please forward your application to jobs@hitechaust.com quoting reference number BL0089. For more exciting job opportunities, visit www.hitechaust.com.

Senior Data Engineer

10-month fixed-term contract - Potential to extend
Marsden Street, Parramatta (hybrid working available)

About Uniting

Our purpose: To inspire people, enliven communities, and confront injustice.
Our values: Compassionate, Respectful, Imaginative, and Bold

At Uniting, we take real steps to make the world a better place. Our focus is always on the people we serve, wherever they are in life.

We deliver services across aged care, disability, child and family services, community services, and chaplaincy, alongside strong social justice and advocacy work. We celebrate diversity and welcome all people regardless of lifestyle choices, ethnicity, faith, sexual orientation, or gender identity.

Uniting is the services and advocacy arm of the Uniting Church NSW & ACT. Our leaders understand, support, and can articulate the mission and purpose of the Uniting Church.

About the role

As a Senior Data Engineer, you will design, build, and maintain scalable, secure, and high-quality data platforms that enable analytics, reporting, and advanced data use across Uniting.

Working within the Data Engineering Chapter in the Data & Analytics team, you will collaborate closely with data analysts, data architects, and business stakeholders. You will provide technical leadership, contribute to architectural decisions, and help uplift data engineering practices to support informed, data-driven decision-making across the organisation.

This role is a 10-month fixed-term contract and reports to the Chapter Lead – Data Engineering, within the Property, Finance & IT directorate.

Key accountabilities

In this role, you will:

Integrate diverse data sources to create trusted, accessible datasets
Architect and implement solutions to support large-scale data processing
Automate data ingestion, transformation, and delivery workflows
Create Power BI Dashboard for Executive oversight
Create detailed reporting to support operational decision making
Monitor system performance, identify bottlenecks, and implement improvements
Apply best practice in data security, access controls, and compliance
Provide technical leadership through code reviews, mentoring, and design guidance
Evaluate and adopt new tools and frameworks to enhance data engineering capability

About you

You are an experienced, hands-on data engineer who thrives in complex environments and enjoys partnering with both technical and non-technical stakeholders. You bring strong problem-solving skills, a collaborative approach, and the confidence to guide technical outcomes while remaining pragmatic and delivery-focused.

As a staff member at Uniting, you actively support diversity and inclusion, working in ways that reflect our values.

Your capabilities

Individual leadership

Takes ownership of outcomes and delivers with a proactive, “can-do” mindset
Works collaboratively to improve performance and ways of working
Remains resilient and focused when navigating complexity
Plans and delivers work within agreed timeframes

Business acumen

Understands Uniting’s objectives and how this role contributes to them
Applies organisational values to day-to-day decision-making
Analyses problems, seeks input where appropriate, and implements effective solutions
Builds strong relationships and influences outcomes without direct authority

Qualifications and experience

Essential

Tertiary qualification in Computer Science, Information Technology, Systems Engineering, or a related discipline, or equivalent professional experience
10+ years’ experience designing, developing, and supporting data engineering, reporting, and analytics
Strong proficiency in Python, SQL, DAX, and Power BI
Proven experience designing and managing ETL/ELT pipelines
Solid understanding of data modelling, governance, quality, and security
Experience working with non-technical stakeholders, demonstrating strong communication, empathy, and insight
Proficiency with Git or similar source control tools
Ability to quickly learn and apply new tools and technologies

Highly regarded

Experience with cloud data platforms, particularly Microsoft Azure (e.g., Azure Data Factory)
Experience with Snowflake, including schema design, performance tuning, and secure data sharing
DevOps and automation experience (e.g., Python scripting, API integration, automated releases)
Exposure to predictive analytics, machine learning, or statistical techniques (Python/R)

Enquiries are welcome, please email Louise Massie at mmassie@uniting.org 




Click here to learn more about our great benefits: Benefits of working at Uniting 




Uniting NSW.ACT contributes to the work and mission of the Uniting Church in NSW and the ACT through social justice advocacy, community services, and spiritual care.

 We provide care and support for people through all ages and stages of life, with a focus on people experiencing disadvantage and vulnerability. Our purpose is to inspire people, enliven communities, and confront injustice.

Uniting is a Child Safe Organisation committed to promoting the safety, well-being, and inclusion of children and young people.

Empowered by diversity
At Uniting, inclusion isn’t just something we value – it’s how we work. Our culture and practice reflect the vibrant diversity of our colleagues, and the clients and communities we serve.

Ad Text:
A career at ASIC will broaden and deepen your already accomplished knowledge, skills and abilities. By working on cutting edge issues, you'll make a difference to our goals, Australia's economic reputation and wellbeing and your own career aspirations 

ASIC's Data Engineering team is seeking a talented Data Engineer to join their team. The successful candidate will support data delivery and data infrastructure across the organisation.

 

Sydney or Melbourne locations
12 & 24 month fixed term positions available
Salary from $127,641 to $149,295 (depending on experience) + 15.4 % superannuation
Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, Sunday 18 January 2026

 

The team 

Information Technology Services delivers a broad suite of IT capabilities and support to ASIC. We are currently driving major technology initiatives that will accelerate our transformation across key areas including virtualisation, data analytics, mobility, and cloud. The Data Engineering team underpins these efforts by providing essential services to our primary stakeholder, the Data & Analytics Office. 

 

The role

As a Data Engineer, you will play a pivotal role in enabling ASIC's data-driven operations. Your responsibilities will include designing and maintaining robust data ingestion pipelines, managing secure and efficient data transfers into ASIC's systems, and ensuring timely and accurate delivery of data to support core business functions. This role is critical to empowering analytics, enhancing operational decision-making, and supporting the broader technology transformation underway at ASIC.

 

More specifically, you will: 

Provide ongoing support for data infrastructure, including the cloud platform, data lake, data marts, and dashboards.
Monitor data platform performance and recommend infrastructure enhancements to maintain optimal benchmarks.
Design and implement ETL pipelines using CI/CD methodologies.
Contribute to the development and deployment of solution designs and big data platform strategies across all environments (development, integration, pre-production, production, and support).
Communicate technical updates and project priorities to leadership, including timelines, budgets, and data technology considerations.
Investigate and resolve data-related incidents promptly.

 

About you

The ideal candidate for this role is a motivated and technically capable Data Engineer who is eager to grow and contribute to ASIC's evolving data landscape. You'll bring hands-on experience with data pipelines, cloud platforms and ETL processes, along with a solid understanding of data infrastructure and performance monitoring. This role is ideal for someone ready to take the next step in their data engineering career while contributing to impactful data and technology transformation projects.

 

In addition, you will have:

Tertiary qualifications in a quantitative discipline such as Statistics, Mathematics, Information Technology, Mechatronic or a related discipline.
Significant experience in data management across cloud platforms, data lakes, warehousing, analytics, and business intelligence.
Proficient with BI and analytics tools such as Databricks, SQL Server, Power BI, R, and Python.
Solid understanding of data warehousing, big data architecture, data streaming, and virtualisation.
Hands-on experience with cloud platforms like AWS, Azure, or GCP.
Strong development skills in Python and SQL.
Experience working within Agile delivery environments.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to resolve complex stakeholder queries.

 

Click ‘apply' to start your application. Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, Sunday 18 January 2026.

 

About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms.

 

ASIC is committed to a providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Indigenous Australians are encouraged to apply as well as applicants from all backgrounds and with different abilities.

 

We offer a range of employee benefits including:

Attractive superannuation
Additional leave entitlements
50/50 hybrid work-from home model
Flexible work arrangements
Assistance for study and professional development

 

Click here to view ASIC's salary and benefits guide.

To read more about ASIC, you can visit our website or review our Corporate Plan.

To work with us, you need to be an Australian citizen and be prepared to complete an ASIC Suitability and Baseline Assessment.

Job Title: Senior Software Engineer (Full Stack), Applied AI
Ad Text:
About MotorPlatform

MotorPlatform is Australia’s fastest-growing B2B automotive marketplace and SaaS platform.

The core platform is built. The next phase is the hard, high-leverage work: scaling product, scaling engineering, and scaling operational excellence, while we shift to being AI-first in how we build and how the platform creates value.

The role

We’re hiring a Senior Full-Stack Engineer to act as Deputy Lead / 2IC in engineering. You’ll be a hands-on builder who can take ownership of major initiatives, lead projects end-to-end, and keep delivery moving with clarity and discipline.

Onsite in Sydney. We want fast feedback loops, high collaboration, and strong product-engineering alignment.

What you’ll be doing (this is a scale role, not a “greenfield” role)

You’ll work on the problems that show up when something is already working and growing fast:

Scale system performance, reliability, and developer velocity as usage expands

Harden security, privacy, observability, and operational runbooks

Build new marketplace capabilities that unlock liquidity, speed, and better dealer outcomes

Reduce friction in critical workflows and improve conversion through product-led engineering

Lead projects that cut across web, mobile, backend, and infrastructure

Improve delivery predictability through planning, coordination, and proactive risk management

Mentor engineers and set the bar for pragmatic, high-quality execution

AI-first: what we expect from you

We’re becoming an AI-first business. That means AI isn’t an experiment on the side—it’s part of the operating system.

You’ll help embed AI into:

Product: smarter workflows, better matching, better quality control, dealer-facing efficiency

Operations: internal tools, automation, knowledge capture, faster support and triage

Engineering: AI-assisted development, testing acceleration, improved reviews, quicker iteration

You’ll partner with our AI/BI team to embed intelligence into the platform and marketplace, including:

Integrating valuation engines into core workflows (pricing, buying, selling, approvals)

Shipping analytics and insights (vehicle acquisition and disposal performance, liquidity signals, margin drivers)

Productionising data/AI services: API contracts, monitoring, quality checks, fallbacks, latency and cost controls

Building internal tools for faster decisions (dashboards, alerts, workflow automation)

You don’t need an ML background. You do need to be comfortable shipping AI-enabled features responsibly and using AI to increase leverage.

Tech stack

Web: React

Mobile: React Native

Backend: PHP (Laravel & Vapor) + Node/TypeScript where it fits

Database: Postgres

Cloud: AWS (EC2, RDS, S3, Lambda)

Delivery: CI/CD, testing, modern development practices

What we’re looking for

Must-haves

Min 6+ years full-stack engineering experience in production

Strong PHP/Laravel (non-negotiable)

Strong React; React Native strongly valued

Strong Postgres fundamentals (schema, migrations, optimisation)

AWS experience (EC2/RDS/S3/Lambda)

Track record leading delivery end-to-end and operating as a senior owner

Highly organised, proactive, and quick to absorb product + industry context

Wants to work onsite in Sydney (Lane Cove)

Nice-to-haves

Marketplace / high-growth SaaS scaling experience

AI-enabled feature delivery (LLM APIs, retrieval/search, automation)

IaC (Terraform/CloudFormation)

Testing frameworks (PHPUnit/Pest, Jest/Mocha)

Why this is a strong next step

The platform is real and growing and your work immediately compounds

You’ll have leadership scope without being removed from building

You’ll help shape how we scale and how we embed AI into the business

You’ll work closely with Product and influence what gets built and why

Location

Sydney (Onsite). Not remote. Not hybrid.

Company description:



About Stanmore Resources

Stanmore Resources is an Australian resources company with world-class operations and exploration projects in the Bowen and Surat basins. Our high-quality mining practices and strong safety and health culture drives our focus on continuous improvement and operational excellence. Creating value for our stakeholders through sustainable development, we have a strong track record of performance in developing, operating and rehabilitating coal resources to produce predominantly export metallurgical coal for steel making. Come and be part of our strong and thriving team.



Job description:



Key Responsibilities

AI Architecture, Engineering & Program Delivery

· Design and build AI systems, agentic workflows, agents, and automation solutions using Azure OpenAI, Semantic Kernel, and modern orchestration frameworks.

· Develop hands-on prototypes, POCs, and production-ready AI components.

· Own the technical architecture for all AI initiatives and ensure alignment with business strategy and platform guardrails.

· Produce reusable AI frameworks (prompts, patterns, agent behaviours, integration flows).

· Provide hands-on engineering support across critical phases of design and delivery.

Chair & Lead the AI Center of Excellence (AI CoE)

· Establish and chair the AI CoE as the enterprise authority on AI standards, governance, and prioritisation.

· Lead the AI CoE operating rhythm:

o Technical standards & architecture reviews

o Governance & guardrails

o Use case intake & prioritisation

o Delivery assurance

o Pattern development & knowledge sharing

· Develop and maintain the Stanmore AI Guardrails, including security, ethical AI, privacy, data controls, and responsible AI.

· Ensure all AI work follows a consistent, repeatable, and scalable delivery model.

· Act as the senior spokesperson for AI architecture across the business.

Integration & Data Architecture (Hands-On)

· Lead and contribute to API development, event-driven patterns, and cloud-native integrations across such as SAP, ServiceNow, Ariba, Minestar, and core corporate/operational systems.

· Build reference solutions using Azure Functions, APIM, Data Factory, Event Hub, and Service Bus.

· Define canonical data models, data contracts, and metadata patterns to support AI, reporting, and operational systems.

· Write or support the development of data pipelines, transformation logic, and ingestion frameworks.

Technical Leadership (Lead by Doing)

· Provide hands-on technical leadership through code reviews, pair programming, and building complex components.

· Coach AI engineers, integration developers, and data engineers.

· Set and promote high standards in engineering, DevOps, IaC, observability, and quality practices.

· Ensure architecture decisions are clearly documented, communicated, and adopted.

Delivery & Execution

· Own major architecture artefacts: solution designs, sequence diagrams, models, patterns, operational readiness artefacts.

· Engage with business partners to shape requirements and convert them into actionable technical plans.

· Support delivery squads with hands-on problem solving and technical guidance.

· Ensure solutions meet performance, security, safety, reliability, and cost objectives.

Standards, Governance & Security

· Maintain enterprise-wide AI and integration patterns, guardrails, and architectural blueprints.

· Ensure responsible AI, cyber security, privacy, and data governance are embedded into every solution.

· Publish and maintain documentation on AI standards, decision frameworks, and supported tools.

· Lead formal architecture reviews and provide final technical sign-off on AI-related projects.

Essential Skills & Experience

Required (Hands-On Capability Mandatory)

· Minimum 10 years across architecture/engineering roles with strong hands-on cloud engineering skills.

· Expert-level implementation experience with Microsoft Azure, including:

o Azure OpenAI

o APIM, Functions, Service Bus, Event Grid

o Azure Data Lake, Fabric, Data Factory

o Azure AI Search & vector databases

· Strong engineering ability in: Python, C#, TypeScript, or equivalent languages.

· Proven experience developing agentic AI workflows using Semantic Kernel, Assistants API, LangChain, LlamaIndex, or similar frameworks.

· Extensive integration architecture experience with large enterprise platforms (SAP, ServiceNow, HRIS, mining systems).

· Demonstrated ability to chair governance forums, lead technical standards, and drive enterprise-wide adoption.

· Excellent communication skills with the ability to engage CIO/GM-level stakeholders.

Desirable Skills

· Azure Architect, Azure AI Engineer, or Data Engineer certifications.

· Experience with MLOps platforms (Azure ML).

· Experience in mining, resources, or operational/asset-intensive industries.

· Familiarity with TOGAF, Agile, or equivalent architecture frameworks.

Role Competencies

· Hands-On Leadership: Leads from the front, diving into technical work when needed.

· Architectural Vision: Understands enterprise priorities, dependencies, and strategic direction.

· Influence & Governance: Able to lead cross-functional groups and enforce technical standards.

· Technical Mastery: Deep skills across AI, cloud, integration, and engineering.

· Strategic Communication: Able to simplify and present complex concepts clearly.

· Delivery Excellence: Balances architectural design with practical execution at speed.

This position is being offered on a contract basis only and does not include permanent employment.

Opportunity to shape the future of mining through cutting-edge data solutions.
Collaborative and inclusive work environment.
Competitive compensation and benefits package.
Commitment to professional growth and sustainability initiatives.

Job description:



● Exciting opportunity to contribute to pioneering work in hearing health

● Location: Macquarie University (hybrid work arrangements considered)

● 12 month - Fixed term Contract, Full time position

Want to improve the lives of Australians, no matter who they are?

Join us and build a career and future you'll be proud of.

Your opportunity

As a Machine Learning Engineer, you will develop impactful solutions. As a key member of our passionate machine learning and AI team within the Signal Processing department, you will drive forward the development of innovative solutions for individuals with hearing loss. Your work will span from creating groundbreaking innovations to applying advanced data analytics to extract valuable insights from our clinical data warehouse. This role is central to our mission of enhancing lives through data-driven innovation. The ideal candidate will have extensive experience programming in Python and a strong foundation in machine learning.

Key responsibilities include:  

ML/AI solution development for hearing health: Prototype, evaluate, and iterate ML/AI approaches (including LLM-enabled systems where appropriate) aligned to hearing health research and product needs as part of multi-disciplinary teams.
Evaluation and validation: Define success metrics; design reproducible evaluation and validation (including for LLM/agent systems) and support responsible, auditable delivery.
Develop and deliver Python solutions: Build and maintain Python applications and services that operationalise ML/AI solutions (e.g., internal tools, APIs, pipelines, agent/tool integrations), with a focus on reliability, testing, and maintainability.
Data understanding for ML: Perform rigorous data analysis to identify signals, define features/labels, detect bias or drift, and translate findings into better ML/AI systems.
Stay updated with the latest advancements in machine learning, AI and its potential applications in hearing healthcare, continuously enhancing skills and knowledge in these areas.

What you'll bring:

We believe the successful candidate will have a proven track record of successfully designing, developing, testing, delivering and supporting commercial products. You'll bring:

Bachelor's degree in engineering, computer science, data science, or related discipline.
Master's degree or PhD desirable
3+ years' experience in a relevant research or industry role (5+ years preferred), with evidence of taking ML/AI work from idea to real-world use (e.g., deployed tools, reliable Python services, or validated research prototypes).
Experience building production-quality Python software, including modular design, testing, version control, and CI/CD practices
Demonstrated research capability through peer-reviewed publications and/or strong independent or collaborative research outputs.
Excellent Python skills
Experience with LLMs and/or NLP, including prompt/tool design, evaluation approaches, and integration into applications.
Strong foundation in machine learning algorithms and principles
Experience in developing, training, and deploying machine learning models
Containerisation experience (e.g., Docker) for packaging and deploying Python applications.
Cloud experience (e.g., Azure; or AWS/GCP equivalent) including deploying and operating services.
Familiarity with CI/CD (e.g., GitHub Actions, Azure DevOps) to automate testing, builds, and deployments.
Familiarity with deep learning frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch)
Ability to demonstrate initiative and creativity
Excellent at taking direction and executing with independence
Excellent written and verbal communication skills
Strong critical thinking skills

What matters most? It's simple - your drive to help anyone and everyone who needs us. And you'll see your role as a real responsibility and an incredible opportunity to make an impact on lives across the country.

Why work at NAL?

The National Acoustic Laboratories (NAL) is a world leader in hearing research and evidence-based innovation to improve hearing health and transform the lives of people with hearing difficulties. NAL collaborates with organisations around the world to innovate on novel solutions to hearing health services and technology, conducts sophisticated validation trials on treatment benefit, and provides insight into the needs of people with hearing loss and clinicians who treat them. NAL's research findings are published in leading peer-reviewed journals and its innovations are used worldwide. NAL is the research division of Hearing Australia.

Visit www.nal.gov.au to discover more!

Job Title: Mechatronics / PLC Programmer & Machine Commissioning Engineer
Ad Text:
Automated Car Stacker Systems

We are a specialist automation company delivering automated car stacker and parking systems across Australia. Due to continued growth, we are seeking a skilled, hands-on Mechatronics / PLC Engineer to join our commissioning and controls team.

This role is suited to an engineer who enjoys building real machines, commissioning on site, and solving complex control problems — not just desk-based programming.

Key Responsibilities

Design PLC control systems from scratch (I/O mapping, interlocks, sequencing, fault logic)

PLC programming using Structured Text and Ladder Logic

Develop, upgrade, and maintain existing and legacy control software

Create and interpret electrical control schematics

On-site commissioning of automated machinery and car stacker systems

Fault finding of control panels, PLCs, sensors, drives, and field devices

Analyse breakdowns and deliver long-term technical solutions

Provide commissioning and critical call-out support when required

Essential Requirements

2–5 years experience in industrial automation / mechatronics

Strong PLC programming skills (Structured Text & Ladder)

Proven machine commissioning experience

Solid understanding of: Interlocks & safety logic , I/O mapping , Motion sequence and Industrial sensors and drives

Hands-on engineering, not just coding – You’ll physically build, wire, and test systems and simulators using real tools, not only program behind a desk.

Physically fit for site work (climbing ladders, lifting equipment)

Must have own vehicle and be available to travel interstate for site work and commissioning

Willing to provide occasional after-hours support

Professional attitude, reliable, and easy to work with

Strong problem-solving skills

Highly Regarded (but not essential)

Experience with automated parking systems, robotics, or material handling equipment

Omron PLC experience is a plus

Safety PLC / machinery safety knowledge

Electrical trade or strong electrical background

What We Offer

We offer the opportunity to work on real, complex automation projects rather than repetitive factory systems, with strong technical ownership and genuine input into system design. You will be part of a small, supportive specialist team working on projects across Australia, with regular site-based commissioning and clear long-term growth opportunities.




To apply, please submit your CV and a short cover letter outlining your relevant experience and why you are interested in this role.
